dct_title_s: [Geological Survey of England and Wales : one inch to the mile map. New Series.] Devizes, drift, sheet 282
dct_description_sm: Geological Survey of Great Britain. Great Britain. Geological Survey of England and Wales. Sheet 282 drift. Great Britain. Ordnance Survey of England. North Decimal Degree 51.350000. South Decimal Degree 51.1833. East Decimal Degree -1.6667. West Decimal Degree -2.0833. In upper left margin: Ordnance Survey of Great Britain. Relief shown by contour interval and spot heights. Transverse Mercator projection. National grid system. "Original geological survey on the one-inch scale by W. T. Aveline. Published on Sheet 14 Old Series, 1857. Resurveyed on the six-inch scale by F. J. Bennett and A. J. Jukes-Browne (N.W. Corner). Printed with Drift, Feb 1899.".
